description:
Valérian and Laureline take on the role of secret agents on behalf of several countries: The former Soviet Union and the USA. From the cold of Siberia to the oases of Tunisia, something seems to link the nuclear operations they're witnessing.

Somewhere else in time, Kistna, an alien with amazing powers believed to be the last of her race, meets Jal.
name: Sur les frontières

description: Published in Hara Kiri between 1961 and 1970. My Dad, or the life of an abused kid and his father, unemployed alcoholic.
name: Mon papa

description: Being human is not funny. But imagine being an animal. Their habitat is contaminated by pollution, we turn their skins into handbags, and after feeding them nicely, they end on the table as a dish!
name: La Vie des bêtes

description: It's the crisis, it's a mess. Reiser is disillusioned, but fortunately, he's resolved to laugh about it all: unfair taxes, social climate, inequality, crises of faith, pollution, consumerism.
name: On vit une époque formidable

description: At the time when Reiser drew Vive les femmes!, relations between the sexes were in full reinvention, thanks to (or because of?) the pill and feminism. A modern woman wants to be man's equal and have as much fun in bed as he does.
name: Vive les femmes!

description: The holidays according to Reiser. Tough and completely unforgettable.
name: Vive les vacances!

description: When Reiser talks about sex, he doesn't hold back. He slices through human, political, and social issues without restraint.
name: Phantasmes

description: Reiser, champion of the modern woman. Les copines is an anthology of cartoons published in Hara-Kiri in the 70s. Here again Reiser glorifies women, the eternal muses of a master of true humor.
name: Les Copines

description: Inspired by a real person who lived next to the Hara Kiri offices, Mr. Gros Dégueulasse appears dressed (or undressed) in just yellow-tinted, smelly, and oversize shorts. He wanders into town, uttering insanities to the public at large.
name: Gros dégueulasse

description: Fous d'amour compiles drawings Reiser devoted to the noble art of male and female encounters. Die of laughter with art from the greatest comedian of all time.
name: Fous d'amour
